From c36fcf49ff0df74b9276b46858720ac15603b56e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2025 16:37:14 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Upstream: DP: ath12k: fix skb_under_panic by pulling headers in all monitor mode skbs

Currently, while enabling monitor mode, the driver removes hardware-specific
headers such as hal_rx_desc, L2 header offset, and packet offset from the
skb->data using skb_pull() in ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload().
However, this operation is only performed on the head MSDU of the skb list.
As a result, the remaining skbs in the list retain the hardware-specific
headers, and their data pointers are not adjusted. When
ath12k_dp_mon_update_radiotap() is later called, skb_push() is used to
prepend the radiotap header. Since skb_pull() was not applied to all
skbs, these skbs do not have sufficient headroom, leading to
skb_under_panic() crash. Fix this by calling skb_pull() for each skb in
the list during ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload(), ensuring that all
skbs have the hardware-specific headers removed and sufficient headroom
is available for skb_push() to safely prepend the radiotap header.

Call trace:
skb_panic+0x48/0x4c
skb_push+0x3c/0x44
ath12k_dp_mon_rx_deliver+0x628/0xb50 [ath12k]
ath12k_wifi7_dp_mon_rx_parse_ppdu_status+0x2f0/0x304 [ath12k_wifi7]
ath12k_dp_mon_rx_dual_ring_process+0x328/0x550 [ath12k_wifi7]
ath12k_wifi7_dp_tx_get_vdev_bank_config+0x4ac/0x564 [ath12k_wifi7]
ath12k_pcic_dummy_irq_handler+0x240/0x47c [ath12k]

Fixes: I371442724ed (UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: add monitor mode support for WCN7850)

Signed-off-by: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>

---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
index 9d8db56..e753765 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
@@ -237,7 +237,7 @@ ath12k_dp_mon_rx_merg_msdus(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev,
 		head_frag_list = NULL;
 
 		while (msdu) {
-			ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload(ab, head_msdu, tail_msdu);
+			ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload(ab, msdu, tail_msdu);
 
 			if (!head_frag_list)
 				head_frag_list = msdu;
@@ -272,7 +272,7 @@ ath12k_dp_mon_rx_merg_msdus(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev,
 		msdu = head_msdu;
 
 		while (msdu) {
-			ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload(ab, head_msdu, tail_msdu);
+			ath12k_dp_mon_rx_msdus_set_payload(ab, msdu, tail_msdu);
 			if (qos_pkt) {
 				dest = skb_push(msdu, sizeof(__le16));
 				if (!dest)
-- 
